## Why This Is Asked
Tests secure, scalable key governance for a multi-tenant real-time analytics pipeline on Azure.

## Key Concepts
- Tenant-scoped CMKs in Azure Key Vault
- Envelope encryption with per-tenant DEKs
- Automated key rotation and governance policies
- RBAC and managed identity-based access control
- Latency optimization through caching and batching
- Observability via Azure Monitor and Purview
- Comprehensive audit trails and compliance logging

## Code Example
```javascript
// Envelope encryption implementation
import { KeyClient } from '@azure/keyvault-keys';
import { DefaultAzureCredential } from '@azure/identity';

const keyClient = new KeyClient(
  process.env.KEY_VAULT_URI,
  new DefaultAzureCredential()
);

async function encryptTenantData(tenantId, data) {
  // Generate per-tenant DEK
  const dek = await crypto.subtle.generateKey(
    { name: 'AES-GCM', length: 256 },
    true,
    ['encrypt', 'decrypt']
  );

  // Encrypt data with DEK
  const encryptedData = await crypto.subtle.encrypt(
    { name: 'AES-GCM', iv: crypto.getRandomValues(new Uint8Array(12)) },
    dek,
    new TextEncoder().encode(data)
  );

  // Wrap DEK with tenant's CMK
  const cmk = await keyClient.getKey(`tenant-${tenantId}-cmk`);
  const wrappedDek = await crypto.subtle.wrapKey(
    'AES-GCM',
    dek,
    cmk,
    { name: 'AES-GCM' }
  );

  return { encryptedData, wrappedDek };
}
```
